// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL8-9_Task_03 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - Tablet 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P808195547" "To any adherents that read this - know that the Count of Misery has broken his bonds and is now drawing upon his blood tribute.  The wards I've placed upon myself are already breaking, and I believe I will shortly be under his sway."
// Answer Text :
"P840109521" "Continue Reading"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P4073912636" "The Count has drawn forth the souls of all the acolytes, but his hunger is insatiable.  He has gone so far as to follow the flows of blood not just to those who have chosen to the take on the Thorn, but down through the generational pathways.  Our young have also been taken!  Not only are our own souls voided to his appetite, but the children's as well!  However, there is still a chance to save us."
// Answer Text :
"P668685407" "Read how to stop the demonic entity"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P3856633991" "The Count of Misery can not be stopped by the flesh alone.  Our empty bodies act as his vessel, him leaping from one to another. Yet, therein lies his weakness.  Were the altars of summoning to be defiled, the souls of his victims could be returned to their bodies.  If all were defiled, he will be weakened enough for a large force of sorcerers to bring him low.  When I am done with this warning, I shall remove my wards and willingly offer my own body as host so that we and our children may be saved."
// Answer Text :
"P1585594525" "Finish reading the tablet"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P1152571883" "Be warned!  The altars must not be destroyed!  Although this would force him into one mortal host, thereby making him weak enough for a singular individual to destroy his corporeal form... It would also tear apart the souls of those he possesses.  Everyone will die with him.<br><br>Adherent, stop the Count of Misery before he gets stronger and follows the generational paths of blood to even those who dwell above -<br><br><color orange>The words on the tablet begin to emit a dull, red glow which spreads up and down the pedestal.</color>."
// Answer Text :
"P1443591496" "Watch the pedestal and tablet"
// Page TerminalSelfDestruct Text :
"P373532400" "<color orange>The glow now covers the entire tablet, bringing forth an unbearable heat."
// Answer Text :
"P897823138" "Step away from the tablet"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - VillainDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2521953135" "*cough*You fight me... Yet I already have your soul."
// Answer Text :
"P905284201" "You did not take my soul, demon!"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P4258470371" "<color orange>The Count of Misery cackles inbetween coughing spasms.</color><br><br>Mortal, I did not need to.  By letting my victims die, you have brought forth as much if not more misery than even I have..."
// Answer Text :
"P2702008573" "They were YOUR victims, not mine!"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P740247644" "Oh, foolish mortal... You and I are already one.  One day you will look in the mirror and see my face... And recognize it as your own.<br><br>Now do what you came here to do... KILL.  ME."
// Answer Text :
"P1454350114" "Dispatch the Count of Misery"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P1539747201" "<color orange>You bend down and break the neck of the host of the Count of Misery with one, quick snap.<br><br>Stepping back up, you see that the body has instantly set into rigor mortis, fixing it's eyes directly upon yours... In a glee-filled grin."
// Answer Text :
"P1698318025" "Walk away..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P1774974989" "How many times will the Circle put innocents in the path of danger during their pursuit of all things unholy? How many times will they need to be stopped, only to do something like this again?  From the sound of the mental scream, you doubt this is a trap... there was too much pain in that cry for help.<br><br>This would be a good opportunity to not only put a stop to the being they unleashed, but also put a stop to the Circle from doing something like this again... permanently."
// AcceptString :
"P4101137713" "Annihilate the cultists and their demonic pet"
// SendOffString :
"P2655250479" "By concentrating on the mental scream, it sounds as if it's coming from down below - most likely from Oranbega.  Head down to that not-so-lost city and find that tablet before taking on the rest of those cultists.  When you're done with them, then it'll just be you and that demon - mano a mano."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P175229540" "Stop the cultists by any means necessary"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3584090181" "If you want to put a stop to this horrific screaming in your mind, you're going to need to take care of those trapped cultists.  Head down to Oranbega and put a stop to them and their demonic ally."
// TaskTitle :
"P4168359599" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Tortured Scream</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P1801642745" "You had better stay on your guard... You don't know what this demonic being is capable of, or how many minions it brought with it."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P3790941034" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Tortured Scream</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>The Count of Misery has been banished back to the hell it came from.  You had to destroy the altars to stop him, killing countless Circle of Thorns worshippers at the same time - but they knew of the dangers that came with summoning a demon.<br><br>Everything the Count said about them was just a load of -<br><br> Lies.  That's all they were.  You're nothing like that demon.<br><br>You're one of the good guys."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P4009273130" "Speak to the Count before dispatching him"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2103182105" "The Count of Misery comes for you!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1165606330" "Fend off the Count of Misery's Host"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P1277981381" "The Count of Misery's host body crumples to ground with a crooked smile and a gleam in its eye..."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P4185461713" "Dispatch the Count of Misery!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3383608100" "Nothing"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P35218549" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>My great ritualist believed that lowly rats such as you could face a god such as I?<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>You do not have the smell of the Thorn upon you, mortal.  A shame, for only they would know the incantation of defilement.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>However, let's take care of this tablet lest one prickled in Thorns does come across this... unfortunate... information."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P2069523866" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>WHAT HAVE YOU DONE, MORTAL?!<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>MY HOSTS!!! You will suffer for this, insignificat insect.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Even with this final host I still have enough power to destroy you for your arrogance.  You have extinguished many lives all for the sole chance of facing me.  Come, mortal, come claim the prize you sorely deserve."
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P61436169" "Hastily Etched Tablet"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P1574626717" "This tablet does not appear to be as old as the rest of the architecture in the surrounding area.  Perhaps it was only recently inscribed upon."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecurityTerminalUsed 
