// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P976151299" "The Count of Misery's Mortal Host"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P2185248221" "Although this is the body of the person you assume wrote the tablet, the thing inside it is instead the Count of Misery.  Strike him down now before he is able to create more armies of hosts!"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1429747023" "Let us now come together and end this, mortal."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P1538578092" "I will relish this dance, mortal."
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2571847547" "Your thoughts..."
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3649262993" "They boil...  they scathe... They cut with jagged strokes..."
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P1751984754" "I was wrong about you, mortal..."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P532647600" "YOU ARE TRULY... ONE... OF... US."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptVillainConfronted 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P2872863585" "Defeat the Count's final host"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P1173650866" "You have stopped the Count of Misery from taking any more lives.  In addition, you have inadvertently prevented the Circle of Thorns from ever summoning him again..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P209376818" "Did you just feel that?  When I walked by {HeroName} I got cold all of a sudden.  It was like I was walking next to the Grim Reaper, himself."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL8-9_Task_04 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - AgentDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2294236711" "Do you think we're going to let you storm in here and just walk out with that little snot?  He'll be long gone before you get anywhere close to him.  Not to mention the poison gas we've rigged the place with in case you get past me."
// Answer Text :
"P3295904112" "No, my plan was for you to help me get to 'little snot'."
// Page AgentPlans Text :
"P2822473279" "HA HA HA!  And just how did you think you were going to do that?!"
// Answer Text :
"P69486042" "Like this..."
// Page AgentIdentification Text :
"P927125614" "<color orange>While applying force to painful pressure points, you choke the Arachnos agent until his eyes roll into the back of his head.  His face reads of a mixture of fear and extreme pain.<br><br>You release him, give him a moment to catch his breath, then do it again.<br><br>And again.<br><br>And again and again.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3877893047" "Now... Tell the Fortunata that the coast is clear and I've got the money."
// Page AgentComm Text :
"P1762470299" "Okay okay okay!  I'll do it... Just... Just please stop.<br><br><color orange>The Arachnos agent stares at you with fear and speaks into his earpiece whilst you press your thumb to his carotid artery, </color>'Fortunata... He's clear... And he has the money.  Should I send him to you now?  Okay, I'll tell him.'<br><br>There... I told her.  Now... let... me........ go.............."
// Answer Text :
"P2600755362" "No."
// Page AgentDeath Text :
"P946531989" "<color orange>You continue to press the artery until he loses all oxygen to the brain, resulting in him collapsing to the floor.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P4060782435" "Leave"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - BossDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P549417137" "I sense not all is as it seems.  You... You seek the brother of Gorzky... But not for him.<br><br>Answer this question, {HeroName}, or I shall call for your unpleasant extermination via quick acting gaseous poison.<br><br>Tell me... Who is it that you seek to exchange this money for their life?"
// Answer Text :
"P2474204086" "Borzky?"
// Answer Text :
"P146431183" "Gustav?"
// Answer Text :
"P2084412788" "Bob?"
// Page PasswordIncorrect1 Text :
"P846959543" "Ah.<br><br>GUARDS!  Activate the gas!<br><br>I'm sorry for you that your foolish plan must now end in death."
// Answer Text :
"P1187093560" "Yours, not mine!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecurityTerminalDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2409698101" "<color orange>This terminal controls the security measures that are intended for stopping any forceful means of rescuing Gorzky's brother.<br><br>From here, you can see a live camera of what appears to be a prisoner being prepared for transportation by a number of Arachnos agents.<br><br>You notice they're standing directly beneath an air duct vent.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3595731495" "Access the terminal"
// Page AccessDenied Text :
"P713303443" "Authorization required - Fortunata alert not yet initiated."
// Answer Text :
"P3134354547" "Ignore the terminal for now."
// Page BaseIsUnderAttack Text :
"P105684107" "<color orange>Looking through this list of function calls, you immediately spot an airflow regulator.  Studying the chart, you're able to see a way to direct the gas away from the area of the base you're in and redirect it to the holding cell.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P4030929029" "Redirect the gas to the holding cell"
// Page SecurityProtocol Text :
"P2058390617" "<color orange>You quickly redirect the gas to the holding cell, and not a moment too soon - your vision is beginning to go a bit hazy.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P958659016" "Check the security cameras"
// Page DestroyBase Text :
"P2862717393" "<color orange>You watch the camera feed and see the group, including who you assume is Gorzky's brother, start to grasp at their necks.  A few moments later, they violently collapse to the ground writhing in horrible spasms.  For several minutes, they convulse wildly on the ground until they abruptly stop.<br><br>It appears as if Gorzky's brother is no longer among the living.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3555827038" "The job is done..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P1300224987" "Judging by the amount of money being swapped for this Gorzky's brother, it's safe to assume there is similar power backing up his threats regarding his brother's safety.  If you were to see this ransom through up to the point where you're in the vicinity of his  brother, you could see to it that Gorzky's fears come true.<br><br>The the cost of one life, you could get an entire foreign power to give Arachnos a taste of their own medicine.<br><br>Besides, it's not like Gorzky's brother probably didn't deserve to be kidnapped  in some way or form.  You can't associate with criminal forces without becoming one yourself.  And it's your job to wipe those lowlifes from the face of this world..."
// AcceptString :
"P397428356" "Turn this unknown foreign power against Arachnos"
// SendOffString :
"P2420462606" "The rest of the instructions in the briefcase detail the location of the ransom and the details of how the ransom is supposed to happen. All you need to do is walk in there, act as if you're working for whoever these guys are, and get close to Gorzky's brother.  One clean hit is all that'll be needed to see to it that Gorzky pursues a blood debt against these tyrants."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3336665837" "Foil the ransom attempt"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P457519261" "The longer you wait to carry out this ransom, the more suspicious Arachnos is going to get. All you need to do is walk in there, act as if you're working for whoever these guys are, and get close to Gorzky's brother.  One clean hit is all that'll be needed to see to it that Gorzky pursues a blood debt against these tyrants."
// TaskTitle :
"P3597367765" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Failed Ransom</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P1215128278" "So far so good.  You're going to need to deal with the guard who's on the lookout.  If you can - convince- him to give you the all clear, you should be able to find the mediator who's doing the exchange."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2336038714" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Failed Ransom</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Although it's dirty work, you've managed to widen a rift between Arachnos and a foreign power.  Yes, you had to assassinate a defenseless person in order to do it.  However, sometimes you have to fight fire with fire.<br><br>Or in this case, with poison."
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P1216403887" "The guard has been subdued.  Now interrogate him!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P3109750604" "Speak to the Ransom Guard"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1621162536" "Find the Fortunata Mistress"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P481603773" "Ransom Guard"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P580327324" "This Arachnos agent is tasked with confirming that you brought all the money in exchange for Gorzky's brother."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3177761604" "{HeroName}?  Are you telling me {HeroName} is the guy they've sent?"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2629531615" "I knew they weren't going to pay the money.  This is a set-up!"
// Script Variable BOSS_1STBLOOD_DIALOG :
"P4188750156" "I'll deal with you first, then let the Fortunata know the ransom didn't go off."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P4107417024" "What do you plan on doing with me now, {HeroName}?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptAgentHealth25 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P2754850625" "Subdue the Ransom Guard"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1485703474" "Fortunata Mistress"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P2000164219" "This Fortunata has been tasked with overseeing the ransom exchange."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P1923538308" "A rather cunning plan, I must admit."
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P1272248649" "But sadly, you fail.  Goodbye, {HeroName}."
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P403662070" "It's too late... Teams are already on their way to relocate him."
// Script Variable BOSS_DEAD_DIALOG :
"P712056863" "You'll never save his life, {HeroName}..."
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P145469893" "I don't understand... Why were you sent?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptBossDead 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P900365541" "Defeat the Fortunata Mistress"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3874034720" "Poison Gas Control Terminal"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P1923139033" "This is the terminal controlling the poison gas."
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P3673501067" "Warning!  Apply gasmasks immediately!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecurityTerminalUsed 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P2488593009" "Stop the poison gas before it's too late!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P2505403716" "You have assassinated Gorzky's brother by using  Arachnos's own technology.  There's no way Gorzky won't believe that Arachnos did it themselves."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P3873582128" "Hey, isn't that {HeroName}?  I heard he was working for some foreign country's military now.  Go figure."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL8-9_Task_05 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - BodyguardDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3540957516" "We're working out of the Rogue Isles to get AWAY from your kind, {HeroName}.  Do your worst... I'll never talk."
// Answer Text :
"P1054401146" "Bend back the Nurse's thumb... Painfully."
// Page TortureMethod1 Text :
"P1347627959" "OW!!!owowowow... OKAY! FINE! I'll talk... What do you want to know?"
// Answer Text :
"P3996521336" "Where is Dr. Hanziger?"
// Page BodyguardTalks Text :
"P2606615431" "Dr. Hanziger? You're here to hurt Jonas?  Well, why didn't you say so?  I never did like that smirk of his - always walking around the place acting like he knew more than you.<br><br>If you're planning on doing half of what you did to me, I'll be more than happy to help.<br><br>Dr. Hanziger is in his office preparing the review of the work we've been doing on kittens and baby pandas recently.  However, only the Chief Neurosurgeon Rodriguez has the authority to page him, and only in case of emergency."
// Answer Text :
"P3977341695" "I'm certain I can convince Rodriguez it's an emergency."
// Page BodyguardLovedOne Text :
"P2107782283" "He's a stickler for protocol, and his kitten/baby panda bear combat models all managed to unlock their cages, forcing us to wear these defensive suits as we exterminated 6 months of his work.  Needless to say, he's in a rather foul mood today.  How do you plan on convincing him it's an emergency?"
// Answer Text :
"P2871830499" "I'll tell him that you're severely injured..."
// Page BodyguardEnd Text :
"P1906636584" "What? But I'm not...<br><br>...oh.<br><br><color orange>With cat-like grace, you put the Head Nurse in a sleeper hold.  You make sure to put the Nurse's body in front of a security camera, knowing they'll send a doctor immediately."
// Answer Text :
"P874554759" "Wuss..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - LovedOneDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P707023764" "It's too late, you know.  We've concluded our experiments and the head doctor is already preparing the results as we speak.  By the time you get to him, he'll already have sent all the data to corporate headquarters.  Not feeling so clever today, are we {HeroName}?"
// Answer Text :
"P952613738" "I'm here for Dr. Hanziger."
// Page LovedOneTalk1 Text :
"P1563193107" "I just told you, {HeroName}, you're not going to find him.  There is no way he's coming out of his office without being given a good reason... And as much as you'd like to belive otherwise, headquarters does not agree that you wiping out our entire base constitutes 'a good reason'."
// Answer Text :
"P3882752575" "Throw Rodriguez the legal papers"
// Page LovedOneTorture1 Text :
"P2005716536" "<color orange>Rodriguez looks through the memos and legal briefs.</color><br><br>Why that no good, dirty, double-crossing, low-down, backstabbing SCOUNDREL!<br><br>GAHHHH!!!  Why didn't I think of doing that!?!<br><br>No no no... There is no way I'm letting that ...opportunist... get away with this.<br><br>Now this... this is what is considered a 'good reason'.  One moment as I page him."
// Answer Text :
"P2381302140" "*Wait for Rodriguez*"
// Page LovedOneTorture2 Text :
"P1039205456" "Grrr!  I'll show him a thing or two.  We've been together on this project for five years.  Five years of dead body after dead body after dead body... And he turns all of this over to the police!?  Without asking me to join in!?  Oh... He's going down... when I get my hands on him I'm going...<br><br>What are you doing with that garotte, {HeroName}?"
// Answer Text :
"P2244356525" "Taking care of the other half of the problem..."
// Page LovedOneEnd Text :
"P1346272462" "<color orange>With a quick tug, you manage to dispatch Rodriguez.  Now the only one left is the man heading up this operation - Dr. Hanziger.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P4243997562" "Find Dr. Hanziger..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - BossDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1911963292" "<color orange>Dr. Hanziger looks down at the red stain slowly spreading from a hole in the middle of his chest, then looks up at you with a questioning expression.</color><br><br>Why, {HeroName}? I thought you were on our side.  I hope however much Crey paid you was worth it..."
// Answer Text :
"P2232138862" "I don't work for Crey.  And you don't deserve immunity, you monster."
// Page BossText2 Text :
"P1180250025" "Monster?  You dare call me a monster?!  After you've destroyed years of careful work and *cough cough* planning - five years of my life gone - five years of other people's lives.  *cough*Families.  After the things I had to do... <br><br>After the nightmares I would wake up from, screaming... every night... gone... and now... now it's too late... Crey's automated security methods have likely already destroyed all the evidence because of your commotion...<br><br>And you - YOU - call me a monster?"
// Answer Text :
"P1049122035" "You can't run from justice Henziger."
// Page MissionEnd Text :
"P2211032143" "<color orange>Dr. Henziger looks down at the gaping wound then slowly looks back up at you.</color><br><br>{HeroName}, I am *cough* 'justice'.<br><br> I've been undercover *cough* for the past five years trying to finally put Crey... away once and...<br><br><color orange>The doctor's eyes stare straight ahead as his wound finally overcomes him.</color>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3928759376" "There is no way you're going to stand idly by as some ghoulish monster with a scalpel gets to walk free on the streets.  Looking through the rest of the briefings, his self-admitted crimes against medicine and humanity are too numerous to list.  Sure, his testimony may help to lock away other Crey monsters, or 'scientists' as they like to call themselves - but is it truly worth letting one of them go due to 'special circumstances', 'national security', and 'pre-emptive presidential pardon'?  Whoever this guy is, he's connected to people in high places.<br><br>Which means that he's got a long way to fall after you 'fix' this issue."
// AcceptString :
"P3473849745" "Prevent Dr. Hanzinger from gaining prosecutorial immunity!"
// SendOffString :
"P437948890" "The documents show that Dr. Henziger is still working within an off-site Crey testing lab in the nearby vicinity.   From the looks of it, the good doctor's snitching hasn't been found out yet by his fellow employees.  You could probably use this to your advantage as you track him down... and silence him permanently."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P1720267724" "Take out Dr. Jonas Hanziger!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P719057996" "You still need to break into the nearby Crey laboratory and track down Dr. Hanziger.  From the looks of it, the good doctor's snitching hasn't been found out yet by his fellow employees.  You could probably use this to your advantage as you track him down... and silence him permanently."
// TaskTitle :
"P2319405643" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Doctor's Orders</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P4247023010" "From all the commotion you can hear down the halls, this is likely the place you'll find Dr. Henziger.  Now all you need to do is find someone to kindly direct you to where the good doctor is."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2420531866" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Doctor's Orders</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>It turns out that all of the special considerations that were being afforded to Dr. Hanziger was due to him being deep undercover, attempting to gather the evidence needed to put Crey Industries on trial.<br><br>What a waste.  It took him five years to do what you did in twenty minutes..."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P174728925" "Get the information from the Head Nurse!"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2624956845" "Find the Chief Neurosurgeon"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1430765454" "Talk with Rodriguez"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P3836644793" "Locate Dr. Hanzinger and defeat him"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1495267993" "Talk with Dr. Hanziger"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1571057338" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Paging Dr. Hanziger.  Please report to the main lab and meet with Dr. Rodriguez."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1151785157" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SteelBlue>This is Dr. Hanziger.  Esteban, this had better be important.  Let me put on my containment suit and I'll be right out."
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3409309713" "Head Nurse Darstin"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P230799641" "This person appears to be the Head Nurse of this laboratory facility.  The Head Nurse will likely know the whereabouts of Doctor Hanziger."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1975490615" "What on earth are you doing here, {HeroName}?"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P1888927365" "We are well within our rights to operate within this location.  YOU are the one violating the law!"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P1594793436" "I... I'm not really trained for combat..."
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P1344988035" "What do you want?!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptBodyguardDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P841729811" "Find the Head Nurse"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2362546563" "Chief Neurosurgeon Rodriguez"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P854697701" "This grumpy looking man must be the main surgeon working out of this laboratory."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P700704309" "{HeroName}... It *was* you on the cameras..."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P1275555367" "What did you do to my Head Nurse, you monster!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2344821568" "You have no right to harass us!  We're performing perfectly legal animal mutation/cloning/splicing experiments.<em t=3>Well, legal here in the Rogue Isles."
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2371088102" "I give up!  I give up!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptLovedOneDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptLairBossAmbush 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P4019613959" "Dr. Jonas Henziger"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P984121055" "The doctor heading up these illicit operations, he's planning on testifying against Crey under the condition that he's granted full immunity."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3477788390" "Esteban? I'm here.  Now out with it.  I have something VERY important I'm doing."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2652410710" "{HeroName}?! Why did they send you for me?  Why wasn't Positron sent to extract me?<em t=3>Wait... You're not here to help me, are you?"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3069438044" "So... Crey found out, didn't they?  After all this time, we were so close..."
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2004413862" "I have to stop you, {HeroName}.  Too much is at stake!"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2577050923" "NO!  You... You're ruining everything..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P824891592" "Dr. Henziger lies dead, and with him so does the last five years of his life.  If he only would have taken care of the problem like you had... He would still be here today."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P933566115" "That's {HeroName}, right?  I hear Crey Industries is has been looking for bounty hunters lately, and every time {HeroName}'s name comes up... Hm..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL8-9_Task_06 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - FoughtFirstHeroBoss 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P4161995301" "Flambeaux's Torn Costume"
// DetailString :
"P3733356620" "You tear a handful of fabric and a little hair from Flambeaux before stashing her unconcious body in a nearby locker.  This should help to convince Polar Shift that Ghoulish Delight is actually the Ghost Twirler in disguise!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - FirstHeroBossDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3988805439" "Oh, wow!  I thought you were going to go all psycho on me there like you're known to do.  So... Why did you help me out?  And what are you doing here, by the way?"
// Answer Text :
"P492550931" "I'm here to put a stop to Ghoulish Delight."
// Page WorkingWithVillain Text :
"P96009738" "Ghoulie? I hate to break it to you, but he's my friend, so I've got his back.<br><br>Okay, maybe 'friend' was a bit too strong of a word.  We're more like partners who like working with each other.<br><br>Hm...<br><br>Okay, 'like' was also not the word I was looking -<br><br>Fine... he's all yours.  So, like, why are you gonna pull the whole Angel-of-Justice-and-Punishment-and-Lurking-and-Brooding act on Ghoulie?"
// Answer Text :
"P615230180" "He's not Ghoulish Delight.  His brother is masquerading as him."
// Page IHaveProof Text :
"P3344150626" "His brother?  You mean that wierdo who twirls that baton around like one of those guys that leads a parade - oh yeah, Ghost Twirler?<br><br>Are you trying to tell me that I've been making out with that wimpy little - Wait a second... This is just a trick, isn't it?  You're trying to distract me and then you're going to do the Mentally Unstable thing after all, aren't you.  Nice try, {HeroName}, but it ain't gonna work.  Whaddya think I'm stupid?"
// Answer Text :
"P2965707218" "Yes.  Quite."
// Page BetrayFirstHeroBoss Text :
"P2739010958" "Oh no you didn't!  That's it!  IT'S ON!"
// Answer Text :
"P2355569899" "Bring it, hot stuff."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecondHeroBossDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P80279679" "Huh?  You don't want to get paid? Then what are you doing here?<br><br>Oh no...<br><br>You're going to try to turn me in to the authorities, aren't you?"
// Answer Text :
"P3144399265" "Nope.  That's Ghoulish Delight's job."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1722972613" "Ghoulish Delight?  You're out of your mind, {HeroName}.  Ghoul is working with us.  Actually, he's the one doing all the real work, to be honest.  He's a bit more gung-ho about this job than he usually is."
// Answer Text :
"P1703992501" "[Show her the costume and tell her the story]"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P3091585866" "I can't believe I was such a fool! Of course that's why he's doing all the work.  All of this was just one huge set-up to arrest us!<br><br>And Flambeaux would be an unholy terror right now if she hadn't already been arrested as you say - I mean, look at how much of her costume was torn!  Anyone who did this would be incinerated on the spot.<br><br>That's it... I'm taking down that fraud by myself!"
// Answer Text :
"P2481987724" "I'll lend a hand this once..."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P2124066871" "When this is all done, maybe you might want to join up with our group.  We could use someone as heartless as you."
// Answer Text :
"P3364369594" "I'm a Hero, Polar Shift... Not evil like you."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P1606192002" "If you remember correctly, Ghoulish Delight has been hanging around with some two-bit lowlifes - Polar Shift and Flambeaux, specifically.  You've been wondering why he's hooked up with their gang, but now it makes sense.  Can you imagine how angry those two might get if they were to find out their 'friend' is actually a hero during the day? Why, you can imagine it might be enough to drive them to do something drastic - like, say, beat him severely at the very least."
// AcceptString :
"P2979307481" "Tell the two twits the secret identity of Ghoulish Delight"
// SendOffString :
"P3407594390" "You're likely not going to be able to convince the two who Ghoulish Delight actually is.  However, if they think he's there to apprehend them, that should be convincing enough."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P1883794472" "Reveal Ghoulish Delight's identity"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1968756731" "You still need to tell the hot and cold twits that Ghoulish Delight is actualy Ghost Twirler. You're likely not going to be able to convince the two who Ghoulish Delight actually is, though.  However, if they think he's there to apprehend them, that should be convincing enough."
// TaskTitle :
"P1514861692" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Two-Timing-Twirler</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P3598039953" "You didn't realize that these idiots have been working *AGAINST* Arachnos.  What were they planning on accomplishing?  It doesn't matter - go find one the airheads and start setting the stage for the dramatic reveal."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P200844744" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Two-Timing-Twirler</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>What was meant to be nothing more than a little lesson in the ways of morality for a hero moonlighting as a villain wound up turning out to be a successful mission all around.<br><br>By targeting a hero rather than a villain, you were able to steal weapons from Arachnos, take down an annoying twit of a villain, and turn another against their other villainous friend. <br><br>Mom would be proud."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2056643075" "Talk with Flambeaux"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1623924346" "Defeat Flambeaux"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P4155676884" "Talk with Polar Shift"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2873239351" "Survive the Arachnos Ambush"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3019448050" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Um... Polar?  Ghoulie?  It's me, Flammie and I'm, um - I think I'm in trouble...<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>So... I found this intercom, right?  The one I'm talking to you on, you know?  But, um, I also found a lot of guards, too.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>And... um... they're looking at me with really angry faces and they're, uh, running towards me really fast, you know?  So, um, I guess what I'm trying to say is... ummm....<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>HEEEEEELLLLLLLPPPPPPMMMMEEEEEE!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3749411149" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>Flambeaux? Where are you, you ditz!  I see the guards on the ground, but I don't see you.  I'm assuming you got to - DAMN!  GHOULISH... THEY GOT ME!"
// Script Variable PET_NAME :
"P2641154310" "Flambeaux"
// Script Variable PET_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3800250308" "{HeroName}? Okay... I don't know if this is a good thing or a bad thing..."
// Script Variable PET_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1705291957" "Over here!"
// Script Variable RescueObjectiveText :
"P3345519135" "Find Flambeaux"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3394053692" "Mu Guardian"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1704193219" "You will open your mind to us and reveal why you are here..."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P3580905586" "Another one of your lot... No matter, we shall collect {HeroName} as well."
// Script Variable SayOnBetrayal :
"P1015376162" "I'm stupid, am I?  Well - well - You're one-hundred percent dumber!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptFirstHeroBossRescued 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
