// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL8-9_Task_07 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - PrometheanSubnetSecurityAccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P3568121056" "Parade Schedule"
// DetailString :
"P3009479528" "This schedule contains all of the events of the parade.  Skimming though the list, you find what you're looking for - a procession of their Warcry robots.  Now all you need to do is find the control console and have them go haywire!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecurityTerminalDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2877456384" "<color orange>You scan through the controller, trying to make heads or tails of what you're looking at.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P2272686474" "Try to decipher the controller."
// Answer Text :
"P2160689823" "Attempt to control the vehicles."
// Answer Text :
"P3388127748" "Access the Mark III robot controls."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1681037714" "You see a variety of different diagnostics readouts regarding a number of different controlled vehicles used in the parade.  These range from cars to robots to floats.  You could spend a long time looking for something without already having an idea in mind."
// Page AccessSubnetDenied Text :
"P4237399009" "Without a clear idea in mind, you could be here all day."
// Answer Text :
"P3306920955" "Locate the Council leader"
// Page AccessSubnetPermitted Text :
"P4196813074" "You find the controls for the Mark III robots.  You see a list of behaviors available to program the robots with.  The current primary behavior is set to 'PARADE' and the secondary is 'BREAKDANCE'."
// Answer Text :
"P266432891" "Set to 'ANNIHILATE' and 'REGENERATE'."
// Page ConfirmOverride Text :
"P3088439803" "You change the behavior settings to the most interesting ones available.  Now... Let's see how Mr. Positron feels about today's parade, eh? <br><br>Last time you checked, murder wasn't 'legal'... And that's exactly what these robots are doing.  The COUNCIL's robots.<br><br>Murdering.<br><br>Which is exactly what they would have done THEMSELVES if you just gave them enough time.<br><br>But it looks like you brought the truth to light, doesn't it?"
// Answer Text :
"P1781037468" "Shut off the Controller to prevent additional deaths."
// Page SelfDestruct Text :
"P2328617481" "<color orange>When you go to shut down the controller, it seems you set off some kind of security device on the terminal... Sending out a call for the return of the robots - straight to the CONTROLLER!"
// Answer Text :
"P2019227116" "Destroy the controller NOW!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P269996424" "So you're supposed to sit there with your thumb up your rear-end while the Council goes on a grand romp all throughout the city?  And Positron thinks you're going to be fine with that?  It looks like he's got another think coming.<br><br>He didn't say anything about sabotaging the event from afar.  Oh, no he didn't."
// AcceptString :
"P1963116704" "Sabotage the Council's parade"
// SendOffString :
"P4176559628" "It shouldn't be too hard to find where the Council is staging their parade from.  Slip in there and find something that can be re-wired, re-routed, or re-purposed... And set it for kill."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P4209794186" "Sabotage the Council's parade!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1151954696" "The Council ain't gonna sabotage their own parade, you know.  Get to their parade staging area and get to work!"
// TaskTitle :
"P251777490" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Heeded Warning</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P2808567818" "From the smell of flowers in the building, it appears as if they're also making floats.  FLOATS!  THE COUNCIL.  HAVING A PARADE WITH FLOATS!<br><br>Not on your watch, they won't."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P3190136216" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Heeded Warning</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>No one tells you whose lives you're going to save and which evildoers need redeeming.  And ABSOLUTELY NO ONE tells you who you're *NOT* going to, either.<br><br>Let this be a lesson to Positron.  He's not the only good guy around here calling the shots.  YOU ARE."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P310397642" "Sabotage the Mark III robots!"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P970118496" "Survive the Mark III onslaught!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P2427572878" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Coming to you from the streets of Paragon City, we have live coverage of today's parade brought to you by the Council.  Bob, what do you make of all this?<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>Well, Frank, I have to say I'm not entirely certain.  I mean, I know the Council have their fair share of controversy from time to time - Look... I'll be honest.  They sure do put on a parade!<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>I have to agree with, Bob.  The way they walk in perfect unison, well, it kinda reminds me of geese in a way, know what I'm saying?!<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>Absolutely, Frank.  Looks like we're in for a good show.  From what I hear they're going to show off some robots that - get this - BREAKDANCE!  I sure am looking forward to that.   But for now, a word from our sponsor."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3955789058" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>I sure was impressed with those floats, weren't you Frank?  A little fact - each one of those floats contained over 200 million petals from flowers around the world - Oh... Are those the robots I see coming up next? Why, yes I think they are!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3931248637" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Have you ever seen anything like that before? I didn't even know that a robot could do the Worm, let alone Moonwalk.  What's this?  Oh ho ho!  They're about to do, you guessed it... The Robot!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P4164333379" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>Ha!  I like the way they're aiming their guns as if they're going - oh no.... <t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>Oh goodness... they're... they're firing... on everyone....<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>No!  NOO! NOOOOO!  RUN EVERYONE!  RUUUUUN!  OH... the bodies... everywhere... they're all... dead..."
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2707734448" "Vortex Cor Leonis Archon"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P589645856" "What is that commotion! We will not have this parade disrupted by silliness!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P799010255" "{HeroName}!  Our parade is fully legal!  You have no right to do this!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecurityBossDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P581402523" "Find the Council Leader and extract information from him"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3608626702" "You have found an itinerary of the parade's events"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3263534699" "Warcry Controller Console"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P4292368298" "This computer is clearly the one that is used to control the Warcry robots."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecurityTerminalUsed 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P3053352799" "Sabotage the Warcry robots from the Controller Console"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1918676839" "Mk III Zenith Warcry"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P1487131876" "This new model of the Warcry has regenerative properties you were unaware of before you tampered with it.  That wouldn't have been so bad were it not for the homing features it was also equipped with as well."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P641370109" "Destination: Searching. Directive: Return to Command Console - brzt - AND ANNIHILATE!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2485975130" "Target: Identifed.  Annihilation: Commencing."
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P478323880" "Auxillary re-routing..."
// Script Variable BOSS_DEAD_DIALOG :
"P3108223639" "Annihilation: Incomplete."
// Script Variable BOSS_KILLEDHERO_DIALOG :
"P3113663054" "Target: Searching.  Database Query: Civilians."
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2608973505" "Rerouting..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptRobotBossDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P4290016265" "You were able to deal with the early arrivals of the Mark III, but there are likely more heading this way.  You might want to leave them as a surprise for Positron."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P492812147" "Looks like {HeroName} was smart and didn't show up to the Council's parade."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL8-9_Task_08 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - AllyConflictDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P229297192" "Again - thanks, {HeroName}.  I should be good from here out.  I used to sometimes flip hospital 'porters around when I needed a quick ride - back when I was filthy scum, wallowing among the dregs of society.<br><br>Since Maelstrom likes to jump around a lot, I just rigged him with a reverse-hospital tag... and tada!  No teleporting!<br><br>I wasn't counting on him doing something similar to me, though."
// Answer Text :
"P169474421" "Why'd you specifically call for me to help you?"
// Page VillainToPrison Text :
"P84578864" "Well, it's because I knew you'd be the one who would do anything to save the day.  It's a bit embarrasing, but I've kinda followed your career. You're the hero I want to be.<br><br>In a way, that's why I was tracking down Maelstrom here.  I did some research and found he's responsible for mass murder when he was still a serviceman.  Now that he's gone rogue, he needs to be put on trial for war crimes."
// Answer Text :
"P864575453" "Back up.  Mass Murder?  Trial?  Explain this now."
// Page VillainToPrison2 Text :
"P2163218293" "Maelstrom here was once in a Black Ops unit for the military.  He carried out all of his orders, but on occasion was known to go to - extremes.  An example of this was a mission where he needed to assassinate a tribal leader.  Instead, he tortured the leader's family - including the children - killing them one by one until the tribal leader came forward to stop him.  Maelstrom proceeded to kill everyone in the village in front of the leader, then sent the elder to other villages to warn them what would happen if they didn't cooperate with the military."
// Answer Text :
"P203455454" "The children.  This monster did that to the children?"
// Page VillainToPrison3 Text :
"P426660528" "Yes, and this is why he needs to be brought before an international court to be tried on multiple violations of various wartime conventions.  Now that we have him, we'll read him his rights and -"
// Answer Text :
"P1275602969" "Rights?  He has forfeited all his rights.  His trial begins now."
// Page VillainToPrison4 Text :
"P4206751844" "Um, {HeroName}?  You can't do that.  He has to be given a fair trial.  If not what's the point of justice?"
// Answer Text :
"P3706390256" "Fairness would be for me to rip his insides out as he screams!"
// Page VillainToPrison5 Text :
"P3813027382" "I'm... I'm sorry, {HeroName}, but you can't do that.  He has to be read his rights and taken before the international community.  If - if you try to harm him - I'll... I'll have to stop you."
// Answer Text :
"P4275294900" "You'd stop me to save this demon's life?"
// Page VillainToPrison6 Text :
"P3303218991" "I'd stop you to see that justice was served, and served fairly.  And to be honest, I'm rather disturbed that you would consider doing something like this.<br><br>You're my hero, {HeroName}.  When did you become this... Twisted, warped vision of what you once were?"
// Answer Text :
"P2475664248" "HOW... DARE... YOU..."
// Page VillainToPrison7 Text :
"P3692515341" "I dare because... Because I'll do what is needed to bring justice to those who wreak havoc on this world.  But I'll do with fairness, to ensure that I am always in the right.<br><br>{HeroName}, please... Please don't make me choose between defending Maelstrom and fighting you..."
// Answer Text :
"P1782681886" "I'll make that choice for you, boy..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - VillainConflictDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2643086279" "I have to say there's not much in this world that shocks me anymore.  However.  That?  That shocked the hell out of me.  You just killed that kid, a kid who looked up to you - who wanted to be you - just so you could... Kill me?<br><br>I haven't seen brass like that since, well... back when I was in that village the kid was talking about.  The look on my face at the time is the same one you're wearing right now.  What the kid left out was that tribe I did that to was responsible for the genocide of several other tribes.  About, oh, ten thousand people, give or take."
// Answer Text :
"P2327624556" "I don't want your stories, only your blood."
// Page FinishHim Text :
"P2114021273" "Wow... Are you already that far down your path?  You know... The one paved with good intentions and all that?<br><br>Don't worry, I got you.  You gotta do what you gotta do, even if you kill kids, right?  I'm totally with you there.<br><br>And by the way, you don't really listen too well, do you?"
// Answer Text :
"P4036499684" "I hear what I need to hear."
// Page FinishHim2 Text :
"P3900054680" "Well, you should've 'needed' to hear more.  The kid just yapped away about how he disabled my teleporter.  That means I could have left anytime.  Which I'll be doing right now.<br><br>Another thing?  The kid ain't dead, had you been listening.  He's probably back at some hospital recovering.  And he'll likely come looking for you one day, hell bent on revenge... kinda like what you're planning to do to me right now."
// Answer Text :
"P1735231964" "You won't get away that eas-"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P466487074" "It's been a while since Blast Furnace was robbing convenience stores and stealing purses from old women.  He's really turned himself around, having taken the road that leads away from hell.  The road you walk, of course.<br><br>But from what you've been hearing lately, though the kid has his heart in the right place, he still doesn't have his head screwed on straight.  Sure he'll do what needs to be done and realizes that sometimes you have to crack some brainpans to make an omelete - well, he's still getting in over his head.<br><br>Why don't you help him out and give him a couple pointers along the way."
// AcceptString :
"P336145728" "Give Blast Furnace some much needed mentoring"
// SendOffString :
"P4197113758" "From what you gathered, it sounds like Blast Furnace is hanging out in some caves below.  His text said something about a beacon which should lead you to where he can be found.  Head over there before your lessons will only fall on dead ears - literally."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3934521053" "Come to Blast Furnace's rescue!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P981666123" "Blast Furnace needs your help!  Get to him quickly or it's curtains for him!"
// TaskTitle :
"P2896707037" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Hasty Text Message</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P2897981202" "The beacon seems to lead to this series of caves.  If only you had a clearer indicator that he was down here somewhere."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P709482093" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Hasty Text Message</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Far up in the sky, you see a streak of flame dart towards the horizon.<br><br>One day that kid's gonna come for you.  He's going to have time to train, to become better. And he'll have the memory of his fallen hero burned in his brain, fueling his every action, his every blow.<br><br>And you'll be waiting right there.<br><br>Waiting.<br><br>Waiting to kick his ass one more time."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P3137032283" "Defeat Maelstrom"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P3199478393" "Talk to Blast Furnace"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1529815536" "Teach Blast Furnace an important lesson"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P4057005330" "Finish Maelstrom"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P2719649868" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick> {HeroName}!  I'm picking you up on my sensors!  I knew you would come!  You always could be counted on to show up at the perfect moment.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Uh-oh... I'm picking up more life-signs.  It looks like my quarry, Maelstrom, is calling in help... from somewhere else.  He's been hiding down here among the Devoured Earth, but... these look different.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>If you can free me from these deceivers of truth and justice, I should be able to help and can explain more then."
// Script Variable PET_NAME :
"P1606485468" "Blast Furnace"
// Script Variable PET_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P4178613266" "Get me out of here."
// Script Variable SayOnRescue :
"P670921548" "I'm so glad you're here!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1390227312" "Maelstrom tagged me with some kind of convection dampener.  In other words, my own armor is preventing me from using my powers.<em t=3>I'll work on removing it, but in the meantime we need to stop Maelstrom while he's wounded so he doesn't teleport away!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P575164988" "Ah!  He attached heat sinks?!  That was it?<em t=3>Okay... I feel really stupid now."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P2627239253" "Why?... What happened to you, {HeroName}?  What have you become?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptHeroAllyRescued 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P4024325054" "Find Blast Furnace"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1197252391" "Maelstrom"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3399760512" "Good one, you walking toaster!  Don't worry... I'll find a way to break out of this."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2479326190" "Ah... You brought a friend.<em t=3> {HeroName}, I'd say it's a pleasure.  But it's not.<em t=3>Now... Let's get this over with."
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P473067867" "I don't need a teleport to kick both - lookin' for something, Red?"
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P1889705709" "Oh, figured out what I did to you, eh boy?"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3978676474" "Alright... I - I - surrender.  Do you want my serial number now, chums?"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1870785470" "By the way... I liked the kid's style a little more than yours..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptVillainDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3426942599" "Maelstrom managed to get away... Again.  However, you were able to teach the kid a lesson about dropping ideals and just doing the job at hand."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P3503520898" "I heard Blast Furnace talking about {HeroName} the other day.  Man... I wouldn't trust that backstabber if my life depended on it... And it seems Blast's did."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL8-9_Task_09 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - ConsortiumSecurityAccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2106184732" "Video Editing Passcode"
// DetailString :
"P1020012033" "This passcode is a root-access level key to all of the video editing and broadcasting equipment throughout the building.  What was intended to immediately stop unwanted broadcasts will be used to do the exact opposite now that it's in your hands."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecurityTerminalDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2635397573" "<color orange>This terminal is connected to a vast array of video editing devices throughout the building.  A variety of functions are available to you from here, ranging from audio, video, and even emergency broadcasting tests, of all things."
// Answer Text :
"P2672599106" "Enter random username/password."
// Answer Text :
"P1489826523" "Alter the video by splicing scenes together."
// Answer Text :
"P1443535529" "Now add audio and dubbing."
// Answer Text :
"P627819036" "Finally, broadcast the new video into the homes of Paragon City."
// Page NoAccess Text :
"P1697774309" "Username/Password incorrect.  Please see the IT administrator for a reset, or the Security Chief in case of emergency."
// Answer Text :
"P2009410082" "Go look for the Chief of Security"
// Page TamperWithMaterials Text :
"P3558449153" "<color orange>You identify a number of scenes from the episode that, if arranged in a different way, would change the context of the entire episode.  Currently the video shows the following:<br><br>[Desdemona banishing a demon then bending down and hugging a crying child] <br><br> [child talks to Desdemona, Desdemona smiles and assures the child, child slowly smiles feeling comforted] <br><br> [Desdemona points to the children dramatically, causing the children to wave in excitement]</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P4078919788" "Arrange the footage to vilify Desdemona."
// Page AccessSecurityFootage Text :
"P3500427645" "<color orange>You arrange the scenes so that it now appears as the following:<br><br> [reverse loop of Desdemona summoning, not banishing a demon] <br><br> [Desdemona pointing to the children] <br><br> [children waving in slo-motion, appearing to gesture 'no'] <br><br> [Desdemona pointing at the children again] - [slo-motion reverse of child smiling, causing the child to look like terror is crossing the child's face as it begins to cry] <br><br> [Desdemona slo-motion smiling] <br><br> [Desdemona hugging the child loop played quickly back and forth to make it look like she's violently attacking the child, or perhaps draining its soul] <br><br> [fade to credits]."
// Answer Text :
"P3213014554" "Now add audio and dubbing"
// Page NotifyTheMedia Text :
"P370539970" "<color orange>Using a number of audio tools, you dub over the existing audio to now match the scenes after they've been edited:<br><br>Desdemona: My minions from Hell will help me to feast upon your souls. <br><br> [points] Which of you children will be food first? <br><br> Children: [waving, in unison] No, please, someone save us! <br><br> Desdemona: [points again]Then I choose to feast on your soul first. <br><br> Child: [child starts crying] No, please.  I trust you, Ms. Desdemona! <br><br> Desdemona:[smiles] Everyone does... <br><br> Desdemona: [attacks child] And I will feast upon ALL of your miserable souls!!! MWHUHAHAHA!</color>"
// Page UnlockRearDoors Text :
"P3485438894" "<color orange>You activate the emergency broadcast system, except you replace the standard video with the one you just edited.  At this moment, everyone throughout Paragon City should be watching the events.  Though they may not be factual, you know them to be true.<br><br><color orange>Suddenly, security alarms start going off throughout the building with a message from the Security Chief directing the search efforts for your person.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3626759390" "Take down the Security Chief again!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3033462711" "You can't even count how many times you've responded to outbreaks of demonic entities, let alone how many times Desdemona was behind them.  It's one thing to convince guillible heroes that she's no longer a threat, but it's another to brainwash small children.  However, if you were to edit this tape so that it shows what you really know was going on in Desdemona's mind... then it would be really hard for her to keep tricking people into believing what she wants them to believe.  You'll be the one controlling the truth, not her."
// AcceptString :
"P2063646283" "Edit the tape of the children's show"
// SendOffString :
"P3965487110" "The best place to take care of this would be the Channel Eight broadcasting affiliates here in the Rogue Isles.  You can edit the tape from there, then send it across their network - beaming it into everyone's home so that all the kiddies... And parents can see what she 'really' is."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P1403833755" "Edit the children's show!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1645567323" "You don't want to wait on getting this video edited. The best place to take care of this would be the Channel Eight studios, who broadcast here in the Rogue Isles to avoid taxes.  You can edit the tape from there, then send it across their network - beaming it into everyone's home so that all the kiddies... And parents can see what she 'really' is."
// TaskTitle :
"P3371410341" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Merlin's Magical Minute</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P3926194480" "It looks like Channel Eight takes their security seriously here in the Rogue Isles.  Instead of hiring people like the Consortium Guards, they've contracted Crey Industries instead.  That means you're going to need to find the head of security in order to access their video-editing machines."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2621564404" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Merlin's Magical Minute</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Even if you had to change the facts in order to tell the truth, you have the best interests of everyone in mind.  Sometimes, in order to do the right thing, you have to do the exact opposite.<br><br>Hmmm... Perhaps that doesn't really make much sense, but with a little editing, you could MAKE that sentence make sense."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P798486825" "Edit the tape on the video editing equipment"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2983157887" "Station Security Chief"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1912964163" "You are not authorized to be in this part of the building."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P242532299" "This is as far as you go."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptFirstBossDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P3168700356" "Defeat the Security Chief"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3379537469" "You have found the passocode needed to access the video-editing machines"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3692226603" "Video Editing Equipment"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P3838421530" "This terminal will grant you access to all of the video editing equipment throughout the building."
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P343387465" "Enter username and password to access this terminal"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecurityTerminalUsed 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P2504452032" "Even if the intruder gets away, I'm holding the security footage, so we can find them later."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P1115793574" "Or... The intruder could come straight to me!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1504196399" "I came prepared this time!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3850768546" "Men!  Apprehend this trespasser immediately!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3874181210" "Good thing I had ANOTHER stimpack!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecondBossDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P2040289790" "Stop the Security Chief once and for all!"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P920788413" "There!  We've got the target in our sights!"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P3636579771" "You're under arrest, {HeroName}!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P2941564648" "Now that you have the footage from the security cameras, it should be safe to leave without anyone knowing you were the one behind telling the public the real truth."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P729933057" "Hey... Isn't that the same {HeroName} that I've heard was trying to frame Desdemona.  Pretty clever!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL8-9_Task_10 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - HeroDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1582053692" "There has to be something we can do for Sky Dragon!"
// Answer Text :
"P650281756" "How do you think they knew Dragon's special weakness?"
// Answer Text :
"P3060485535" "Look at the display and tell me what you see."
// Page TooLenient Text :
"P2568209662" "Weakness?  Wait... Was that a band made from Ultra-Magnesium?  Oh no... It was, wasn't it?<br><br>I sure hope they didn't let it set in the moonlight for nine days while it soaked it the tears of wise men.  Dragon told me that would strip him of his powers permanently.   I was the only one he trusted that information to, come to think of it.<br><br>Wait... what was the question again?"
// Answer Text :
"P3232865024" "*sigh*I asked you how you think Malta found out about the Band?"
// Page TooLenient2 Text :
"P2425147556" "I have no idea.  That information is a closely guarded secret, and no one is ever supposed to be told about it.<br><br>uh...<br><br>Kinda like what I just did.  Oh, man... I'm so stupid.  My grandma would smack me silly if she found out.  Heck, if she found out that I was a superhero, she would have a heartattack!<br><br>Wait... where was I?  Sky Dragon!  {HeroName}!  We have to save him!"
// Answer Text :
"P1626048753" "Follow me.  I think I know a way."
// Page TeachingALesson Text :
"P3672472393" "...grandma?  GRANDMA!<br><br><color orange>The display shows a live feed taken from Flamespout's house.  Several Malta soldiers are ransacking the place, searching for something important.  In the center of the room, oen soldier has a weapon pointed at Flamespout's grandmother.  She looks distressed as she clutches the left side of her chest.</color><br><br>"...ohmygod... That's my house!  AND THEY'RE HURTING MY GRANDMOTHER!"
// Answer Text :
"P880793864" "Let's try this again... How do you think they found her?"
// Page TeachingALesson2 Text :
"P1395614295" "What does it matter?  They have my grandmother!?  And she looks like she's hurt!  It's like... It's like this was one big huge trap to get Sky Dragon and me!"
// Answer Text :
"P1302449625" "Bingo!  One last time... How. Did. They. KNOW!?"
// Page TeachingALesson3 Text :
"P2137396184" "I don't know, okay!?  I mean, maybe I told a couple of people about Sky Dragon's weakness, okay? But they were friends of mine!<br><br>And I also told my online friends that I was Flamespout, but I only have three hundred of those kinds of friends, it's not like I have a thousand - and not ONE of them is into Malta! <br><br>Oh, yeah... and I told my tribe  in that one computer game I play, too. BUT THAT'S IT!  I didn't think it was going to hurt anyone!<br><br>DON'T WORRY GRANDMA!  I'M GONNA SAVE YOU!  JUST HANG ON, OKAY!<br><br>{HeroName}, please... we gotta save my grandma!"
// Answer Text :
"P3844746510" "I'll take care of it..."
// Page TeachingALesson4 Text :
"P1431100027" "<color orange>You pull out a walkie-talkie and a voice disguising device.  You say, 'Strike Team Delta has found target.  All teams evacuate the area'.  At the same time, the image shows the leader of the Malta group barking orders then everyone clearing the room.</color><br><br>'Wait a second... they just left after you told... Wait....<br><br>You were behind this, {HeroName}?  But... but why?"
// Answer Text :
"P586448065" "To teach you a lesson about keeping your mouth shut, you idiot!"
// Page TeachingALesson5 Text :
"P2567366514" "Hold on... You had Sky Dragon depowered and kidnapped, risked my life so you could 'rescue' me, had my home invaded, AND put my grandmother in grave danger because... Because...<br><br>...You wanted to 'teach' me a lesson?"
// Answer Text :
"P1293329515" "Just imagine how things COULD'VE gone if I were actually a Villain?  Furthermore..."
// Page TeachingALesson6 Text :
"P3321662822" "<color orange>You explain to Flamespout that you had Sky Dragon taken to a hospital.  You explain that you got all the information you needed on Flamespout's profile page, and told him that if he doesn't straighten up he'll get someone killed.  You also tell him that Malta was given orders to kill no civilians, so his grandmother was safe the whole time. </color>"
// Answer Text :
"P687599867" "You're lucky it was me doing this, not a villain."
// Page TeachingALesson7 Text :
"P67757117" "<color orange>At that moment, the woman in the image clutches her chest even tighter than before.  A look of fear crosses her face, then she slowly slumps to the ground... Unmoving.  You look back at Flamespout and see murder in his eyes. </color><br><br>YOU.  ARE.  A.  VILLAIN!"
// Answer Text :
"P1472986171" "Watch your mouth, kid.  One more word and I'll kill you..."
// Page TeachingALesson8 Text :
"P1316954994" "<color orange>Flamespout lunges at you!</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1097058073" "Teach the kid the ultimate lesson."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3817646693" "You getting sick and tired of all these new sidekicks showing up and then texting, friending, and tooting - or whatever it is they call it - to every Tom, Dick, and Harry that they're 'fighting crime'.  The punks don't realize that any villain can just as easily get that information and do horrible things with it.<br><br>In other words, hyper slack-offs are considered cannon fodder to the kind of guy that'll kill you if you look at them wrong.  Maybe you can't change this new generation of 'heroes', but you sure can scare the holy terror out of this one and set him straight."
// AcceptString :
"P3002016633" "Set up the sidekick and scare the daylights out of him."
// SendOffString :
"P3462375988" "With a couple of calls, mysterious nighttime meetings, and a host of other preparations you manage to set up the perfect lesson for this little snot.<br><br>Let class begin."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3222975341" "Teach Flamespout a few lessons about villains"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P2227464188" "You haven't yet dealt with Flamespout's irresponsible foolishness.  With a couple of calls, mysterious nighttime meetings, and a host of other preparations you manage to set up the perfect lesson for this little snot.<br><br>Let class begin."
// TaskTitle :
"P811371562" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Dragon's Whelp</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Villain Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P1550111629" "From the sound of it, Malta took the bait.  Let's hope they've already managed to overcome Sky Dragon by using those Ultra-Magnesium bands you anonymously sent them. Now... To find Flamespout."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2820096050" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The Dragon's Whelp</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Everything in your lesson to that kid went off without a hitch.  You just weren't expecting his grandmother to be so... well, frail.<br><br>In the end, the kid didn't pay attention to the most important lesson:<br><br>Watch what you say.  It just might get you killed."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1492716936" "Talk to Flamespout"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2931761623" "Kill Flamespout"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P100940305" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SteelBlue>Please!  Let him go!  You're hurting him... what did you... do to him?<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Shut up, punk!  I'm sick of your whining.  We got what we came for... now to get rid of you.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SteelBlue>Oh man... pliers?  What... what are you going to do with the pliers?..."
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_NAME :
"P2024397005" "Flamespout"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3017351219" "Gunslinger"
// Script Variable SayOnRescue :
"P1891008582" "{HeroName}? They got Sky Dragon!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3932096698" "What are we going to do?  They used this weird thing on Dragon and he disappeared.  I think they... They disintegrated him..."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1826962540" "A holograph?  How is this going to help us?"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1348588496" "YOU MONSTER!!!  You... You're WORSE than a villain!"

